description:
&lt;p&gt;Benenden Hospital has a proud history, dating back to 1907, when it was set up to treat postal workers with TB. It is now a modern, contemporary hospital situated in the heart of the Wealden countryside and provides a wide range of medical, surgical and healthcare services to private and NHS patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are difficult times and we are seeking additional volunteers to join our family and help us with today&#39;s challenges. Our Meet and Greet team play a crucial part in keeping our patients and visitors safe and feel welcomed and supported during their visits, and we are looking for friendly people who want to make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our spacious CQC Outstanding hospital has a rigorous hygiene and cleaning routine and is a COVID-secure workplace.  To keep you safe, we have all the required precautions in place including social distancing, protective screening, PPE and one-way systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can spare a few hours a week, we can use your talents.  Please apply to join our team of volunteers or give us a call to discuss further.&lt;/p&gt;
